
# <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# Type:
# build:    Changes to build system, dependencies, or project tooling
# chore:    Routine maintenance tasks (git hooks, .gitignore, etc.)
# ci:       Changes to CI configuration and scripts
# docs:     Documentation changes only
# feat:     New features or significant functionality additions
# fix:      Bug fixes and error corrections
# perf:     Performance improvements
# refactor: Code improvements
# revert:   Reverting a previous commit
# style:    Code style changes (formatting, missing semicolons, etc.)
# test:     Add or refactor tests
#
# Scope (optional):
# - A noun describing the scope of the commit change
# - Example: feat(parser): add ability to parse arrays
#
# Description:
# - A short summary of code changes in imperative mode
# - Limit to 50 characters
#
# Body (optional):
# - Provide additional information about the code changes
# - Explain *what* and *why* (not *how*)
# - Wrap at 72 characters
# - Use dashes (-) for bullet points
# - Can use multiple paragraphs
#
# Footer (optional):
# - BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
# - Close/Fixe/Resolve: #<issue-number>
# - Reviewed-by: Bob <bob@example.com>
#
# Breaking Changes:
# - Indicated by a ! after the type/scope and immediately before the `:`
# - Included as a footer
